---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Uuumi App"
  description="How the Uuumi app handles your data. Learn what we collect, how we use it, and your rights."
>
  <main class="legal">
    <div class="container content">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: April 30, 2026</p>

      <section>
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          Uuumi ("we", "our", "us") is a screen time management app with a virtual pet,
          operated by Jan Podmolík. This policy explains what data we collect, how we use it,
          and your rights regarding that data.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you have any questions, contact us at
          <a href="mailto:info@uuumi.app">info@uuumi.app</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Information we collect</h2>

        <h3>Account information</h3>
        <p>When you create an account, we collect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Email address</strong> — provided directly or through Sign in with Apple / Google</li>
          <li><strong>Authentication data</strong> — securely managed by our backend provider (Supabase)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          If you use Sign in with Apple, you can choose to hide your real email address.
        </p>

        <h3>App data synced to the cloud</h3>
        <p>To enable cross-device sync and backup, we store the following on our servers:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Pet information (name, evolution history, daily stats)</li>
          <li>Screen time goals and limit settings</li>
          <li>Aggregated usage statistics (total daily usage, hourly summaries)</li>
          <li>Break history (duration, type, completion)</li>
          <li>Coin balance and unlocked content</li>
          <li>User preferences and settings</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Data that stays on your device</h3>
        <p>The following data is <strong>never sent to our servers</strong>:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Names of specific apps, websites, or categories you use</li>
          <li>Individual app usage data and tokens from Screen Time / Family Controls</li>
          <li>Detailed per-app screen time breakdowns</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We only sync aggregated usage totals — we never know which specific apps you use or for how long.
        </p>

        <h3>Analytics</h3>
        <p>
          We use <strong>PostHog</strong> to collect product analytics, such as which features are used,
          purchase events, and app lifecycle events. PostHog runs on the EU instance
          (eu.posthog.com), so analytics events are processed and stored within the European Union.
          Events are tied to your account ID once you sign in; before sign-in they are tied to an
          anonymous device-generated identifier.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do <strong>not</strong> use session replay, screen recording, or heatmaps. We do not
          track you across other apps or websites. You can opt out of analytics at any time in
          <em>Profile → Privacy</em> within the app.
        </p>

        <h3>Purchases</h3>
        <p>
          All payments are processed by <strong>Apple</strong> through the App Store. We do not collect,
          process, or store any payment information. We only receive confirmation of your subscription
          or purchase status from Apple.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>How we use your data</h2>
        <p>We use the information we collect to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide and maintain the Uuumi app and its core features</li>
          <li>Sync your progress across devices</li>
          <li>Process and manage your subscription</li>
          <li>Improve the app through product analytics</li>
          <li>Respond to your support requests or feedback</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Third-party services</h2>
        <p>The Uuumi mobile app uses the following third-party services:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Supabase</strong> — authentication and cloud data storage</li>
          <li><strong>PostHog (EU)</strong> — product analytics, processed within the European Union</li>
          <li><strong>Apple (Sign in with Apple, StoreKit)</strong> — authentication and in-app purchase / subscription processing</li>
          <li><strong>Google (Sign in with Google)</strong> — authentication when you choose Google as your sign-in method</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not sell your personal information to third parties. The mobile app does
          not contain any advertising networks, tracking pixels, or third-party advertising SDKs.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Advertising and tracking</h2>
        <p>
          The Uuumi mobile app does <strong>not</strong> use the device's advertising identifier
          (IDFA) and does <strong>not</strong> track you across other companies' apps or websites.
          The privacy manifest distributed with the app reflects this (no tracking declared).
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Data retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain your data for as long as your account is active. If you delete your account,
          your account record and all linked personal data — including pets, settings, coin
          balance, and aggregated usage history — are permanently removed from our servers via
          cascading database deletion.
        </p>
        <p>
          Any feedback or support messages you previously submitted are retained in
          anonymized form (with your user identifier removed) so that we can continue improving
          the App. Local data on your device is cleared upon sign-out.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Data security</h2>
        <p>
          We protect your data using industry-standard measures, including encrypted connections (TLS),
          row-level security policies on our database, and secure authentication flows. However, no
          method of electronic storage or transmission is 100% secure.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Uuumi is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal
          information from children under 13. If you believe a child has provided us with personal
          information, please contact us and we will delete it promptly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>Depending on your location, you may have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access the personal data we hold about you</li>
          <li>Correct any inaccurate data</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
          <li>Restrict or object to processing of your data</li>
          <li>Export your data (data portability)</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent at any time</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You can delete your account and all associated data directly within the app
          (Profile → Delete Account). For any other requests, email us at
          <a href="mailto:info@uuumi.app">info@uuumi.app</a> and we will respond within 30 days.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Notifications</h2>
        <p>
          Uuumi uses <strong>local notifications only</strong> — they are generated on your device
          and never pass through our servers. We do not use push notification services. You can
          manage notification permissions in your device settings at any time.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>This website (uuumi.app)</h2>
        <p>
          The marketing website at uuumi.app is separate from the mobile app and uses
          <strong>Google Tag Manager</strong> to load analytics and marketing tags subject to your
          consent. We use Google Consent Mode v2: by default, analytics, advertising, and
          personalization cookies are <em>denied</em> until you make a choice in the cookie banner.
        </p>
        <p>
          The cookie categories are:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Necessary</strong> — basic site functionality such as theme preference. Always on.</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics</strong> — helps us understand how visitors use the site.</li>
          <li><strong>Marketing</strong> — used for advertising measurement and remarketing on third-party platforms.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You can change your cookie preferences at any time via the "Cookie Settings" link in
          the site footer. Your choice is stored locally in your browser. The mobile app is not
          affected by website cookie settings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Governing law</h2>
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy is governed by the laws of the Czech Republic. If you are located in
          the European Economic Area or the United Kingdom, you also retain all rights granted to
          you under the GDPR or UK GDPR, including the right to lodge a complaint with your local
          data protection authority.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make significant changes,
          we will notify you through the app. The "Last updated" date at the top of this page
          reflects the most recent revision.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Contact us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at
          <a href="mailto:info@uuumi.app">info@uuumi.app</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal {
    padding-top: 4rem;
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
    min-height: 100vh;
    background: var(--bg-primary);
  }

  .content {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .back-link:hover {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .updated {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  li {
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-hover);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
